White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
Playing Games With Me
I ran into a second buckeye butterfly that was on the dirt path in front of me.  I already had a good shot of an earlier one so didn't intend to take another photo.  However, it kept flying ahead of me a few feet, landing directly in my path and spreading its wings so I finally gave in and took this shot.  Who knew buckeyes were such camera hams?
